<slide>
<title>Importing data</title>

<blurb>MongoDB is schema less, so fits the OSM data model quite well, but you still
need to think about how to store the data best:</blurb>
<example>$doc = array(
	'name' => 'A440',
	'tags = [
		'highway' => 'secondary',
		'oneway' => 'yes'
	]
);

$db->poi->ensureIndex( [ 'name' => 1 ] );
$db->poi->ensureIndex( [ 'tags.highway' => 1 ] );
$db->poi->ensureIndex( [ 'tags.oneway' => 1 ] );</example>
<blurb>or:</blurb>
<example>$doc = array(
	'name' => 'A440',
	'tags' = [
		{ 'k' => 'highway', 'v' => 'secondary' },
		{ 'k' => 'oneway', 'v' => 'yes' }
	]
);

$db->poi->ensureIndex( [ 'name' => 1 ] );
$db->poi->ensureIndex( [ 'tags.k' => 1, 'tags.v' => 1 ] );</example>
